Here is the cleaned up text:

You are here: 
Salesforce Help
Docs
Salesforce Release Notes
Marketing Cloud Account Engagement

Send operational emails through Engagement Studio, copy assets directly to Salesforce CMS, and view account alerts in Optimizer. If you use the Engage for Gmail Chrome extension, make a transition plan before June 2024.

Send Operational Emails to Opted-Out Prospects Directly from Engagement Studio
You can now send non-marketing emails to opted-out prospects directly from Engagement Studio.
Copy Images to a Salesforce CMS Workspace
Transfer your images to a Salesforce CMS workspace for future marketing initiatives.
View Alerts in the Optimizer
Access alerts and feature recommendation banners within the Account Engagement Optimizer.
Account Engagement API: New and Changed Items
Access more of your data with updates for version 5 of Account Engagement API.
Engage for Gmail Chrome Extension Is Being Retired
The Engage for Gmail extension is projected to retire in June 2024 due to Google disabling Manifest V2 Chrome extensions.
title: Marketing Cloud Account Engagement Features in Summer '24
